BONUS:

Disabling & dangerousness: go hand in hand with dysfunction because if the behavior and mindset get out of control, your mental state can deteriorate to the point of your body (over or underweight) being put at great risk of disease and death. 

/end

Deviance: anything not considered the norm. (Complicated because of changing norms, but basically anything you’d prefer to do in private.)
Ex. Calculating calories and BMI constantly, wanting to weigh food, not accepting/believing your TDEE/BMR and going over or under by a lot...

Distress: if pursuing your behavior causes yourself stress. 
Ex. Calorie math at every meal, shame/anger/depression after eating, anxiety at the thought of eating/being seen in front of others or the possibility of those two

the desire to punish/shame yourself after eating.

Dysfunction: if your behavior is enough to affect your life in some major way. 
Ex. Turning down invitations to hang out with friends, being hesitant to eat at gatherings, refusing to leave the house because of how you perceive your body

& feeling isolated as a result of these.

+also there are 2 bonus D’s (disabling and dangerousness) which I’ll address too

Let’s make my developmental psych minor worth the money i paid. (A thread w/ some examples)
